item.title: I need help with everything!
item.dc:creator: @mlgsnipe mlgsnipe
item.description:
@mlgsnipe wrote:

Umm from readin wut u wrote i suspect that ur talking about “gui”.
So you have to go into your CLIENTS FILES and find “gui”
Next search for: Serverip
It might be like: Serverip = “themanscape.no-ip.biz”;
So Just repplace the whole thing with 0.0.0.0 or 127.0.0.1
(this are all default ips)
If u want people to play on your server u have to portforward and get a different ip… that a different thing.
So in the end it should end up like this:
Serverip = “0.0.0.0”;
or…
Serverip = “127.0.0.1”;
Save, exit and compile. Run your server and then run your client and it should be working

EASY CODING.
